e h1b y28a ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws5ec">Other scriptures on that dirty, wrinkled scrap of paper spoke of God’<span class="_ _e"></span><span class="ws0">s</span></div><div class="t m0 x2b h1b y1ce ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws5ed">desire for Boldera to repent. Boldera knelt in the tall brown prairie grass</div><div class="t m0 x2b h1b y1cf ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and pra<span class="_ _0"></span>y<span class="_ _0"></span><span class="ws406">ed to this God whom he did not yet kno<span class="_ _0"></span><span class="ws0">w<span class="_ _2"></span>. “Creator of the sk<span class="_ _f"></span>y<span class="_ _2"></span>,<span class="_ _7"></span>Y<span class="_ _f"></span>ou</span></span></div><div class="t m0 x2b h1b y1d0 ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">hav<span class="_ _0"></span><span class="ws5ee">e spoken to me. I repent and ask <span class="_ _f"></span><span class="ws0">Y<span class="_ _f"></span>ou to forgi<span class="_ _1"></span>v<span class="_ _0"></span>e my sins. Car<span class="_ _6"></span>ry me on</span></span></div><div class="t m0 x2b h1b y1f0 ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Y<span class="_ _f"></span>our shoulders as Y<span class="_ _15"></span><span class="ws1f8">ou did that lost sheep. Be my Shepherd.<span class="_ _2"></span><span class="ws0">”</span></span></div><div class="t m0 x1e h1b y1f1 ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws5ef">God led Boldera from his perch atop his pony to the city of Darkhan,</div><div class="t m0 x2b h1b y28b ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws22f">Mongolia, where he met other Christian belie<span class="_ _0"></span><span class="ws0">vers. There he learned more</span></div><div class="t m0 x2b h1b y1f2 ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws5a2">about the Savior to whom he had pra<span class="ws0">y<span class="_ _0"></span><span class="ws550">ed. He g<span class="_ _0"></span><span class="ws0">a<span class="_ _0"></span>v<span class="ws550">e his life to Christ and</span></span></span></span></div><div class="t m0 x2b h1b y1f3 ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">pledged to follow Him wherever He led.</div><div class="t m0 x1e h1b y1f4 ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">F<span class="_ _0"></span><span class="ws5f0">our years later Boldera continues to worship God in Darkhan. <span class="_ _2"></span><span class="ws0">T<span class="_ _2"></span>oday he</span></span></div><div class="t m0 x2b h1b y6 ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws1a5">is a soft-spoken teenager, leader of his 43-member <span class="_ _2"></span><span class="ws0">Y<span class="_ _15"></span>outh Ali<span class="_ _0"></span>v<span class="_ _0"></span>e club.</span></div><div class="t m0 x1e h1b y28c ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws44c">Boldera still has that tattered scrap of paper that led him to God. And he</div><div class="t m0 x2b h1b y1f5 ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">has a special burden to reach the other Mongolian shepherd boys with the</div><div class="t m0 x2b h1b y1f6 ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws5f1">gospel. He wants them to know the Creator and recognize His voice when</div><div class="t m0 x2b h1b y1f7 ff79 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">He speaks. </div><div class="t m0 x2b h28 y1dc ff78 fs1f fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">John McGhee is Sabbath School and Personal Ministries Director for the Northern Asia-</div><div class="t m0 x2b h28 y165 ff78 fs1f fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">P<span class="_ _2"></span>acific Division. </div><div class="t m0 x2d h24 y108 ff82 fs1c fc0 sc0 ls0 ws105">Produced by the General Conference Office of Mission Awareness </div><div class="t m0 x2d h24 y109 ff82 fs1c fc0 sc0 ls0 ws106">E m a i l : g o m i s s i o n @ c o m p u s e rv e. c o m</div><div class="t m0 x25 h2 y10a ff78 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">87</div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
